Grammy award-winning rapper, Cardi B, has officially announced that she will be coming to Nigeria for the first time The 27-year-old made the announcement on her Instagram page. The rapper will be performing live in Lagos, Nigeria and Accra, Ghana for Livespot X Festival on December 7 and 8, 2019, respectively. Cardi B on her Instagram page wrote: “Africa, I’m coming! Nigeria and Ghana.” Cardi B who is married to rapper, Offset is famous for her hits such as ‘Bodak Yellow’, ‘I like it’ and ‘Money’. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.